    <summary>In June 2011, Gavin Andresen received a report about the ClearCoin CSRF vulnerability and confirmed that it was fixed. Doug Huff reported multiple CSRF vulnerabilities in http://clearcoin.appspot.com, which could be exploited by staying logged into Google account. The site is run by Gavin Anderson who is known as the lead Bitcoin maintainer. In light of recent events, Douglas Huff decided to report these vulnerabilities publicly instead of private disclosure of issues. He provided test cases and proof of concept code for the CSRF vulnerabilities.</summary>
